ciscoItpDsmrSmppMIB.name: ciscoItpDsmrSmppMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoItpDsmrSmppMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems, Inc Customer Service Postal: 170 W. Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-ss7@cisco.com
ciscoItpDsmrSmppMIB.description: The MIB for providing information about Distributed Short Message Routing delivery using Short Message Peer-to-Peer protocol. Acronyms and Terms DSMR Distributed Short Message Routing SMPP Short Message Peer-to-Peer (protocol) SMS Short Message Service UCP Universal Computer Protocol. WRR Weighted Round Robin. A variation of the round robin algorithm that uses server weights to allow uneven distribution of traffic among a set of available servers. ********************************************

CdsmrSmppInactivityTimer.name: CdsmrSmppInactivityTimer
CdsmrSmppInactivityTimer.description: This textual convention defines the allowed values used to define Inactivity timer used by Short Message Peer-to-Peer session. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that an object has not been set to value and that the default value is to be used.

CdsmrSmppResponseTimer.name: CdsmrSmppResponseTimer
CdsmrSmppResponseTimer.description: This textual convention defines the allowed values used to define response timer ,in milliseconds, used by Short Message Peer-to-Peer session. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that an object has not been set to value and that the default value is to be used.

CdsmrSmppSendWindow.name: CdsmrSmppSendWindow
CdsmrSmppSendWindow.description: This textual convention defines the allowed values used to define send window used by Short Message Peer-to-Peer session. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that an object has not been set to value and that the default value is to be used.

CdsmrSmppSessionInitTimer.name: CdsmrSmppSessionInitTimer
CdsmrSmppSessionInitTimer.description: This textual convention defines the allowed values used to define session initiation timer used to create Short Message Peer-to-Peer session. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that an object has not been set to value and that the default value is to be used.

CdsmrSmppBindType.name: CdsmrSmppBindType
CdsmrSmppBindType.description: List of possible bind types. 'none' : Bind type not specified. 'any' : Allow receipt of any SMPP bind type, send transceiver binds 'receiver' : Receive or send SMPP receiver binds only 'transceiver': Receive or send SMPP transceiver binds only 'transmitter': Receive or send SMPP transmitter binds only

CdsmrSmppKeepaliveTimer.name: CdsmrSmppKeepaliveTimer
CdsmrSmppKeepaliveTimer.description: This textual convention defines the allowed values used to define keep alive timer used by Short Message Peer-to-Peer session. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that an object has not been set to value and that the default value is to be used.

cdsmrSmppSessionStateNotifEnable.name: cdsmrSmppSessionStateNotifEnable
cdsmrSmppSessionStateNotifEnable.description: A control to enable or disable notifications as follows: 'true' Indicates that the ciscoItpDsmrSmppSessionState notification should be generated.. 'false' Indicates that ciscoItpDsmrSmppSessionState notification generation is disabled.

cdsmrSmppProfileTable.name: cdsmrSmppProfileTable
cdsmrSmppProfileTable.description: A table that is used to monitor specific information used to configure short message peer-to-peer protocol profile. Entries are added to this table via cdsmrSmppProfileRowStatus in accordance with the RowStatus convention.

cdsmrSmppProfileTableEntry.name: cdsmrSmppProfileTableEntry
cdsmrSmppProfileTableEntry.description: Each entry defines parameter that can be used to default values for sessions.

cdsmrSmppProfileName.name: cdsmrSmppProfileName
cdsmrSmppProfileName.description: A name used to define a collection of parameters for short message peer-to-peer protocol. A name that is used to identify a unique SMPP profile.

cdsmrSmppProfileBindType.name: cdsmrSmppProfileBindType
cdsmrSmppProfileBindType.description: Specifies allowed types of binds for session.

cdsmrSmppProfileInactivityTimer.name: cdsmrSmppProfileInactivityTimer
cdsmrSmppProfileInactivityTimer.description: This object defines the allowed values used to define inactivity timer used by Short Message Peer-to-Peer session. Indicates the maximum time lapse allowed time between transactions before destination is considered inactive. The value for this object should be two to three times the value specified for the cdsmrSmppProfileKeepaliveTimer object.

cdsmrSmppProfileKeepaliveTimer.name: cdsmrSmppProfileKeepaliveTimer
cdsmrSmppProfileKeepaliveTimer.description: This object defines the allowed values used to define keep alive timer used by Short Message Peer-to-Peer session.

cdsmrSmppProfileCallingParty.name: cdsmrSmppProfileCallingParty
cdsmrSmppProfileCallingParty.description: This object is used to indicate presence of optional calling party option.

cdsmrSmppProfileResponseTimer.name: cdsmrSmppProfileResponseTimer
cdsmrSmppProfileResponseTimer.description: This object defines the allowed values used to define response timer used by Short Message Peer-to-Peer session. This is the amount of time to wait before retransmitting packet.

cdsmrSmppProfileSendWindow.name: cdsmrSmppProfileSendWindow
cdsmrSmppProfileSendWindow.description: This object defines the allowed size of send window used by Short Message Peer-to-Peer session window.

cdsmrSmppProfileSessionInitTimer.name: cdsmrSmppProfileSessionInitTimer
cdsmrSmppProfileSessionInitTimer.description: This object defines the allowed values used to define session initiation timer used to create Short Message Peer-to-Peer session. This specifies the maximum amount of time to wait for the session Bind to be received.

cdsmrSmppProfileRowStatus.name: cdsmrSmppProfileRowStatus
cdsmrSmppProfileRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cdsmrSmppProfileTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cdsmrSmppSessionTable.name: cdsmrSmppSessionTable
cdsmrSmppSessionTable.description: A table that is used to collection information on short message peer-to-peer protocol sessions. Entries are added to this table via cdsmrSmppSessionRowStatus in accordance with the RowStatus convention.

cdsmrSmppSessionTableEntry.name: cdsmrSmppSessionTableEntry
cdsmrSmppSessionTableEntry.description: Each entry defines parameter and state information on short message peer-to-peer protocol sessions.

cdsmrSmppSessionLocalPortNumber.name: cdsmrSmppSessionLocalPortNumber
cdsmrSmppSessionLocalPortNumber.description: Local port number used to establish short message peer-to-peer protocol.

cdsmrSmppSessionLocalIpAddrType.name: cdsmrSmppSessionLocalIpAddrType
cdsmrSmppSessionLocalIpAddrType.description: This object contains the type of the local IP address used to create an session.

cdsmrSmppSessionLocalIpAddress.name: cdsmrSmppSessionLocalIpAddress
cdsmrSmppSessionLocalIpAddress.description: This object contains the local IP address used to create the session with the partner of this session.

cdsmrSmppSessionDynamicDest.name: cdsmrSmppSessionDynamicDest
cdsmrSmppSessionDynamicDest.description: Indicates whether dynamic destinations are allowed as follows. 'true' - dynamic destination are allowed. 'false' - dynamic destinations are not allowed.

cdsmrSmppSessionRowStatus.name: cdsmrSmppSessionRowStatus
cdsmrSmppSessionRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cdsmrSmppSessionTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cdsmrSmppDestTable.name: cdsmrSmppDestTable
cdsmrSmppDestTable.description: A table that is used to define a collection of information on short message destinations. One or more destination is defined under each session using peer to peer protocol. Entries are added to this table via cdsmrSmppDestRowStatus in accordance with the RowStatus convention.

cdsmrSmppDestTableEntry.name: cdsmrSmppDestTableEntry
cdsmrSmppDestTableEntry.description: Each entry defines parameter and state information on short message peer-to-peer protocol destinations.

cdsmrSmppDestName.name: cdsmrSmppDestName
cdsmrSmppDestName.description: A name used to uniquely identify a destination using short message peer-to-peer protocol.

cdsmrSmppDestBindType.name: cdsmrSmppDestBindType
cdsmrSmppDestBindType.description: Specifies allowed types of binds for session.

cdsmrSmppDestInactivityTimer.name: cdsmrSmppDestInactivityTimer
cdsmrSmppDestInactivityTimer.description: This object defines the allowed values used to define inactivity timer used by Short Message Peer-to-Peer session. Indicates the maximum time lapse allowed between transactions before destination is considered inactive.

cdsmrSmppDestKeepaliveTimer.name: cdsmrSmppDestKeepaliveTimer
cdsmrSmppDestKeepaliveTimer.description: This object defines the allowed values used to define keep alive timer used by Short Message Peer-to-Peer session.

cdsmrSmppDestCallingParty.name: cdsmrSmppDestCallingParty
cdsmrSmppDestCallingParty.description: This textual convention is used to indicate presence of optional calling party option.

cdsmrSmppDestResponseTimer.name: cdsmrSmppDestResponseTimer
cdsmrSmppDestResponseTimer.description: This object defines the allowed values used to define response timer used by Short Message Peer-to-Peer session. This is the amount of time to wait before retransmitting packet.

cdsmrSmppDestSendWindow.name: cdsmrSmppDestSendWindow
cdsmrSmppDestSendWindow.description: This object defines the allowed size of send window used by Short Message Peer-to-Peer session.

cdsmrSmppDestSessionInitTimer.name: cdsmrSmppDestSessionInitTimer
cdsmrSmppDestSessionInitTimer.description: This object defines the allowed values used to define session initiation timer used to create Short Message Peer-to-Peer session. This specifies the maximum amount of time to wait for the session Bind to be received.

cdsmrSmppDestRemotePortNumber.name: cdsmrSmppDestRemotePortNumber
cdsmrSmppDestRemotePortNumber.description: Remote port number used to establish short message peer-to-peer protocol session.

cdsmrSmppDestRemoteIpAddrType.name: cdsmrSmppDestRemoteIpAddrType
cdsmrSmppDestRemoteIpAddrType.description: This object contains the type of the remote IP address used to create an session.

cdsmrSmppDestRemoteIpAddress.name: cdsmrSmppDestRemoteIpAddress
cdsmrSmppDestRemoteIpAddress.description: This object contains the remote IP address used to create the session.

cdsmrSmppDestProfileName.name: cdsmrSmppDestProfileName
cdsmrSmppDestProfileName.description: Specifies Profile from cdsmrSmppProfileTable table to define common default parameters for destination.

cdsmrSmppDestState.name: cdsmrSmppDestState
cdsmrSmppDestState.description: Current state of destination. 'active' - Destination is available. 'inactive' - Destination is unvailable. 'open' - Device is listening on port for destination to establish connection.

cdsmrSmppDestSentRequests.name: cdsmrSmppDestSentRequests
cdsmrSmppDestSentRequests.description: Number of SMS requests sent to destination.

cdsmrSmppDestRcvdRequests.name: cdsmrSmppDestRcvdRequests
cdsmrSmppDestRcvdRequests.description: Number of SMS requests received from destination.

cdsmrSmppDestSentResponses.name: cdsmrSmppDestSentResponses
cdsmrSmppDestSentResponses.description: Number of SMS responses sent to destination.

cdsmrSmppDestRcvdResponses.name: cdsmrSmppDestRcvdResponses
cdsmrSmppDestRcvdResponses.description: Number of SMS responses received from destination.

cdsmrSmppDestRowStatus.name: cdsmrSmppDestRowStatus
cdsmrSmppDestRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cdsmrSmppDestTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

ciscoItpDsmrSmppSessionState.name: ciscoItpDsmrSmppSessionState
ciscoItpDsmrSmppSessionState.description: This notification is generated whenever UCP destination changes states. This notification provides information on the availablity of the destination to receive and process packets using the SMPP protocol.

ciscoItpDsmrSmppMIBCompliance.name: ciscoItpDsmrSmppMIBCompliance
ciscoItpDsmrSmppMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Cisco CISCO-ITP-MLR-MIB

ciscoItpDsmrSmppGroup.name: ciscoItpDsmrSmppGroup
ciscoItpDsmrSmppGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information used to configure Short Message Peer-to-Peer Protocol.

ciscoItpDsmrSmppNotificationsGroup.name: ciscoItpDsmrSmppNotificationsGroup
ciscoItpDsmrSmppNotificationsGroup.description: DSMR Short Message Peer-to-Peer Protocol notification objects.
